  "quest.collection.trinkets.title": "&d&l1&r | Trinkets",
  "quest.transport.car.2448508ABDA0650D.desc_1": "Holding a &bPart Scanner&r in your hand will highlight &eyellow&r and &7grey&r boxes on vehicles, which indicate places where vehicle parts can be &binstalled&r.",
  "quest.transport.car.2448508ABDA0650D.desc_2": "Looking at the boxes will cause the scanner to beep, as well as show a list of compatible parts for that location.",
  "quest.transport.car.2448508ABDA0650D.desc_3": "&cNote:&r &7Installed parts will &cnot&r &7show a box until removed using a wrench!",
  "quest.transport.car.2448508ABDA0650D.subtitle": "You're going to need it.",
  "quest.transport.car.293059BE5778EEBA.desc_1": "The &bEngine Bench&r is used for making vehicle engines.",
  "quest.transport.car.293059BE5778EEBA.desc_2": "Most vehicles &calready come with an engine installed&r, but may accept different types of engines. This is useful if you plan to change a vehicle to use a different fuel.",
  "quest.transport.car.293059BE5778EEBA.desc_3": "&7Be sure to check which components your vehicle can accept using a &bPart Scanner&r &7before you craft them!",
  "quest.transport.car.2E83858BC28DCF9C.desc_1": "The &bInstrument Bench&r is used for making vehicle instruments.",
  "quest.transport.car.2E83858BC28DCF9C.desc_2": "Most vehicles &calready come with instruments&r, but different instruments can be swapped in by &6[Right-Clicking]&r the vehicle with a&b Wrench&r. ",
  "quest.transport.car.41646396CA1E93F6.desc_1": "The &bCustom Bench&r is used for crafting miscellaneous car accessories.",
  "quest.transport.car.4799AC42E072C1F9.desc_1": "The chassis of most vehicles can be crafted at a &bVehicle Bench&r. ",
  "quest.transport.car.4799AC42E072C1F9.desc_2": "To make them fully functional, however, you will need to also need to craft &bwheels&r, &bseats,&r and &bengines&r at their respective benches.",
  "quest.transport.car.4799AC42E072C1F9.desc_3": "&cNote:&r &7Consider scavenging or restoring existing vehicles, as the materials required for some of the recipes are quite complex!",
  "quest.transport.car.4799AC42E072C1F9.desc_4": "&cNote 2:&r &7Some vehicles come with parts pre-installed! Consider crafting something like the &bQuad&r &7from the &bMTS Official Vehicle Pack&r &7if you prefer a working vehicle straight away.",
  "quest.transport.car.4799AC42E072C1F9.subtitle": "Guess we're also making aircraft now.",
  "quest.transport.car.51BCD4B6ECA6B159.desc_1": "The &bSeat and Cargo Bench&r is used for making vehicle seats and additional cargo storage.",
  "quest.transport.car.51BCD4B6ECA6B159.desc_2": "Some vehicles come pre-installed with seats, but most will need at least &eone&r seat (the driver's seat) in order to function.",
  "quest.transport.car.51BCD4B6ECA6B159.desc_3": "&7Be sure to check which components your vehicle can accept using a &bPart Scanner&r &7before you craft them!",
  "quest.transport.car.556596D1041BBF84.desc_1": "Most vehicles require &eGasoline&r or &eDiesel&r, depending on the engine type. ",
  "quest.transport.car.556596D1041BBF84.desc_2": "This can be pumped into a &bFuel Pump&r from the bottom.",
  "quest.transport.car.556596D1041BBF84.desc_3": "To use the Gas Pump, &6[Right-Click]&r it. ",
  "quest.transport.car.556596D1041BBF84.desc_4": "If there is a valid vehicle nearby, it will automatically connect and start fueling it. ",
  "quest.transport.car.556596D1041BBF84.desc_5": "&cWARNING:&r Fuel cannot be removed from an existing vehicle! Swapping the engine will reset the fuel in it.",
  "quest.transport.car.556596D1041BBF84.subtitle": "Car go Vroom",
  "quest.transport.car.58E74F8ACDA26EC3.desc_1": "The &bWheel Bench&r is used to make wheels and tracks.",
  "quest.transport.car.58E74F8ACDA26EC3.desc_2": "Some vehicles come pre-installed with wheels, but most will need at least &efour&r in order to function.",
  "quest.transport.car.58E74F8ACDA26EC3.desc_3": "&7Be sure to check which components your vehicle can accept using a &bPart Scanner&r &7before you craft them!",
  "quest.transport.car.58E74F8ACDA26EC3.subtitle": "The wheels on the bus go round and round...",
  "quest.transport.car.5C7E426CF8809DBC.desc_1": "The &bGun Bench&r is used for crafting turrets, some guns, and vehicle ammunition.",
  "quest.transport.car.5E08E03EFECCB48D.desc_1": "The &bPropellor Bench&r is used for crafting aircraft propellors.",
  "quest.transport.car.66C317B602394D81.desc_1": "The &bDecor Bench&r is used for crafting blocks unique to MTS.",
  "quest.transport.car.7793BC0CCE7D3ECE.desc_1": "Used to craft the &bFuel Pump&r. Can also be used to transfer fuel between vehicles.",
  "quest.transport.car.7C4F4514B19ADCCE.desc_1": "The &bWrench&r allows you to configure a vehicle's &bdashboard&r, as well as &buninstall&r parts and/or &bpick up&r the vehicle itself.",
  "quest.transport.car.7C4F4514B19ADCCE.desc_2": "&6[Left-Click]&r while looking at a part to uninstall it.",
  "quest.transport.car.7C4F4514B19ADCCE.desc_3": "&6[Right-Click]&r the vehicle to open up the dashboard configuration UI.",
  "quest.transport.car.7C4F4514B19ADCCE.desc_4": "&6[Shift+Right-Click]&r to set the vehicle's license plate.",
  "quest.transport.car.7C4F4514B19ADCCE.desc_5": "&6[Shift+Left-Click]&r to pick up the vehicle (turn it into an item).",
  "quest.transport.car.7C4F4514B19ADCCE.subtitle": "Oh god, ANOTHER wrench",
  "quest.transport.car.manual.desc_1": "&bVehicles&r can spawn in various states of disrepair in the cities, waiting to be restored.",
  "quest.transport.car.manual.desc_2": "Most vehicle parts will need to be made in their respective crafting benches, then installed on the vehicle chassis using a &bWrench&r.",
  "quest.transport.car.manual.desc_3": "&cNOTE:&r &7This guide will walk you through the basics, but be sure to read the mod manual for more information!",
  "quest.transport.car.manual.subtitle": "Get ready, it's a lot of words.",
  "quest.transport.car.manual.title": "Cars 101",
  "quest.transport.car.subtitle": "Reinventing the wheel.",
  "quest.transport.car.title": "Automobiles",
  "quest.transport.planes.blueprint.desc_1": "In order to build planes, you must first find the blueprint for the &bAircraft Engine&r.",
  "quest.transport.planes.blueprint.desc_2": "It can be found in the &eWasteland&r.",
  "quest.transport.planes.blueprint.subtitle": "Here's one way to fly...",
  "quest.transport.planes.blueprint.title": "Taking Flight",
  "quest.transport.planes.eco_engine.desc_1": "The Eco Engine is an optional aircraft upgrade that changes the performance of your aircraft's engine.",
  "quest.transport.planes.eco_engine.desc_2": "§bNOTE:§r Like all Immersive Aircraft upgrade, it takes up an upgrade slot!",
  "quest.transport.planes.eco_engine.title": "Eco Engine",
  "quest.transport.planes.engine.desc_1": "This modpack contains two different plane mods, §6Immersive Aircraft§r and §6Simple Planes§r.",
  "quest.transport.planes.engine.desc_2": "However, both mods use a common engine block to power their aircraft.",
  "quest.transport.planes.engine.desc_3": "Feel free to check the entries for the respective aircraft to have a better understanding of which one is more suitable for you!",
  "quest.transport.planes.engine.subtitle": "Key to the Sky",
  "quest.transport.planes.engine.title": "Aircraft Engine",
  "quest.transport.planes.ia_upgrades.desc_1": "&6Immersive Aircraft&r upgrades are split into two categories, &bAircraft Weapons&r and &bAircraft Upgrades&r.",
  "quest.transport.planes.ia_upgrades.desc_2": "Each type of aircraft can only hold a certain amount of each category, so plan well!",
  "quest.transport.planes.ia_upgrades.title": "Immersive Aircraft Upgrades",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.airship.desc_1": "&7Slow but easy to maneuver.&r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.airship.desc_2": "Weapon Slots: §b1§r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.airship.desc_3": "Upgrade Slots: §b3§r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.airship.desc_4": "Cargo Slots: §b16§r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.airship.title": "Airship",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.biplane.desc_1": "&7Fast and rather reliable. Make sure your runway is long enough.&r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.biplane.desc_2": "Weapon Slots: §b1§r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.biplane.desc_3": "Upgrade Slots: §b4§r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.biplane.desc_4": "Cargo Slots: §b16§r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.biplane.title": "Biplane",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.cargoairship.desc_1": "&7Slow and fuel hungry, but carries an entire storage.&r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.cargoairship.desc_2": "Weapon Slots: §b0§r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.cargoairship.desc_3": "Upgrade Slots: §b4§r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.cargoairship.desc_4": "Slots: §b80§r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.cargoairship.title": "Cargo Airship",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.hopper.desc_1": "&7A chonky aircraft with three seats and pontoons to land safely on water.&r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.hopper.desc_2": "Weapon Slots: §b2§r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.hopper.desc_3": "Upgrade Slots: §b4§r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.hopper.desc_4": "Cargo Slots: §b16§r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.hopper.title": "Bamboo Hopper",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.quadrocopter.desc_1": "&7Perfect for building, and that's about it.&r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.quadrocopter.desc_2": "Weapon Slots: §b1§r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.quadrocopter.desc_3": "Upgrade Slots: §b1§r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.quadrocopter.desc_4": "Cargo Slots: §b6§r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.quadrocopter.title": "Quadrocopter",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.warship.desc_1": "&7A flying fortress, slow but heavily armed.&r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.warship.desc_2": "Weapon Slots: §b2§r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.warship.desc_3": "Upgrade Slots: §b6§r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.warship.desc_4": "Cargo Slots: §b66§r",
  "quest.transport.planes.immersiveaircraft.warship.title": "Warship",
  "quest.transport.planes.manual.desc_1": "&bImmersive Vehicles&r also allows for the creation of &baircraft&r, which while simpler to make are &cquite complex to fly&r.",
  "quest.transport.planes.manual.desc_2": "They can be made from the &bVehicle Bench&r.",
  "quest.transport.planes.manual.desc_3": "We recommend practicing in creative, or using &bImmersive Aircraft&r instead.",
  "quest.transport.planes.manual.subtitle": "And here's another...",
  "quest.transport.planes.manual.title": "Planes 102",
  "quest.transport.planes.nether_engine.desc_1": "The Nether Engine is an optional aircraft upgrade that changes the performance of your aircraft's engine.",
  "quest.transport.planes.nether_engine.desc_2": "§bNOTE:§r Like all Immersive Aircraft upgrade, it takes up an upgrade slot!",
  "quest.transport.planes.nether_engine.title": "Nether Engine",
  "quest.transport.planes.title": "Planes",
  "quest.transport.train.1DE6001A10454C74.subtitle": "Obtained by looting or sequenced assembly.",
  "quest.transport.train.2A3F96302E68B66A.desc_1": "The &btrain station&r allows you to assemble your train, among other things. ",
  "quest.transport.train.2A3F96302E68B66A.desc_2": "Ponder it with &6[W]&r to get a more detailed tutorial!",
  "quest.transport.train.2A3F96302E68B66A.subtitle": "For all your train scheduling needs",
  "quest.transport.train.358DC7C7A1EF9AD4.desc_1": "Alternatively, try to restore the existing railway system for fast travel!",
  "quest.transport.train.358DC7C7A1EF9AD4.subtitle": "Obtained by looting or sequenced assembly.",
  "quest.transport.train.495CE9D070CBC0DE.subtitle": "Obtained by looting or sequenced assembly.",
  "quest.transport.train.4B96A3DF7F541D30.desc_1": "The &btrain casing&r is used in many train-related blocks. Craft one by using a sturdy sheet on a brass casing.",
  "quest.transport.train.4B96A3DF7F541D30.subtitle": "Also try Factorio!",
  "quest.transport.train.4F409A5069158D18.subtitle": "Obtained by looting or sequenced assembly.",
  "quest.transport.train.6B85E8592B0BB1D8.desc_1": "The &btrain controller&r allows you to actually control your train. ",
  "quest.transport.train.6B85E8592B0BB1D8.desc_2": "Place a seat, sit in it and &6right click&r the controller to start driving.",
  "quest.transport.train.6B85E8592B0BB1D8.subtitle": "Multi-track drifting!",
  "quest.transport.train.title": "Trains",
  "quest.transport.train.train_assembly.desc_1": "Successfully assemble a train using the &btrain station&r.",
  "quest.transport.train.train_assembly.subtitle": "Full steam ahead!",
  "quest.transport.train.train_assembly.title": "All Aboard!",
  "quest.transport.train.train_fuel.desc_1": "Trains require fuels such as &bcoal&r placed in chests or barrels on them to be able to move.",
  "quest.transport.train.train_fuel.subtitle": "Steam power comes in the next patch",
  "quest.transport.train.train_fuel.title": "Train Fueling"
}
